ampus Map       Search                 View Menu  Down arrow icon            Breadcrumbs   College of Nursing    Programs & Applying    Bachelor of Science in Nursing        Bachelor of Science in Nursing  The Nurse Generalist  A BSN degree from UIC will provide you with the strongest possible foundation for a fulfilling career as a nurse—one of the fastest growing and most trusted professions in the U.S. Here at UIC, you'll learn from some of the nation’s foremost nursing leaders and be supported by energetic and engaged peers.      First, tell us where you stand now           Wish to become a nurse?  Our traditional program is a hands-on, in-person college experience.             Already a licensed RN?  Our transitional, online RN to BSN completion program is for you.           What our students say        “The BSN program is challenging. But beyond the scientific aspect, a lot of our classes try to delve deeper into social aspects of nursing, including LGBT and racial issues. It’s really refreshing to have those conversations, and I think that’s unique to the UIC experience.”    Franc Louie de Guzman | BSN Class of 2019          “UIC Nursing is one of the top nursing programs in the nation. The faculty here are very supportive and have endless knowledge to help you out throughout the program. I am grateful to have gotten into UIC nursing and have no regrets at all.”    Timothy Le | BSN Class of 2019          What can I do with a BSN?   Whether it’s your entry into the nursing field or just into our college’s incredible community, your UIC BSN is only the beginning.    Non-RNs, sit for the exam to become licensed    Progress to the DNP    Join an incredible alumni community        Take the next step        Learn about the traditional BSN program          Check out the RN to BSN program              Programs & Applying    Back to main content           Find Your Program     Bachelor of Science in Nursing     Traditional BSN     Meet BSN students    Admissions & App